  "doc_id": "844",
  "text": "We used a home-built high-speed AFM apparatus [CITATION_1] . The cantilevers (Olympus) were 6-7 mm long, 2 mm wide, and 90 nm thick. Their spring constant was $0.1 Nm À1 , and their resonant frequency and quality factor in water were 0.8-1 MHz and $2, respectively. For AFM imaging, the free oscillation amplitude was $1 nm and the set-point amplitude was around 90% of the free oscillation amplitude. The tapping force estimated was less than 30 pN [CITATION_2] . The probe tip was grown on the tip of a cantilever with electron beam deposition and was further sharpened by argon plasma etching [CITATION_3] .",
